The paper presents a new artificial neuron model capable of learning its receptive field in the spatial domain of inputs. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) as it deals with the development of a new neuron model. Additionally, the paper uses tests on synthetic and real datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) or Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of stochastic gradient descent optimization, which is a common optimization technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions tests on the MNIST dataset, which is a commonly used dataset in Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper does not focus on language processing, it is less likely to belong to this sub-category.
